1
00:00:10,833 --> 00:00:14,133
Obviously, Emma is not
in her right mind.

2
00:00:14,267 --> 00:00:16,500
She's insane.

3
00:00:16,633 --> 00:00:17,900
You need to find her.

4
00:00:18,033 --> 00:00:20,700
- Her again?
- I want you to scare her.

5
00:00:20,833 --> 00:00:23,433
Make her paranoid
until she goes crazy.

6
00:00:26,500 --> 00:00:27,233
You're crazy!

7
00:00:29,867 --> 00:00:31,467
Where have you been?
What happened to you?

8
00:00:32,300 --> 00:00:33,333
Demon!

9
00:00:33,500 --> 00:00:35,033
She seems to be paranoid.

10
00:00:35,167 --> 00:00:37,967
You told Olive's henchman
to follow me to the woods!

11
00:00:38,100 --> 00:00:40,933
- Let go of me!
- Mom!

12
00:00:41,067 --> 00:00:41,933
Emma, hold on!

13
00:00:43,200 --> 00:00:45,067
Danilo, you need to decide.

14
00:00:45,200 --> 00:00:46,933
Look at what's happening
to Emma.

15
00:00:47,067 --> 00:00:48,200
This isn't right anymore.

16
00:00:48,333 --> 00:00:50,467
What we'll do
is for your own good.

17
00:00:50,600 --> 00:00:51,500
This is for you.

18
00:00:51,633 --> 00:00:52,933
Mookie!

19
00:00:53,067 --> 00:00:55,733
Mookie!

20
00:01:34,533 --> 00:01:36,667
Let go of me! Take this off!

21
00:01:38,367 --> 00:01:39,933
- Just come with us.
- I'm not crazy.

22
00:01:40,067 --> 00:01:41,467
I'm begging you!

23
00:01:41,633 --> 00:01:43,967
Bring me back to my family!
I'm begging you!

24
00:01:44,100 --> 00:01:45,233
Bring me back to them!

25
00:01:45,367 --> 00:01:47,900
This place will drive me crazy
even more! What the heck!

26
00:01:49,900 --> 00:01:51,167
What are you doing?

27
00:01:51,300 --> 00:01:55,233
Let me go. Stop!

28
00:02:00,233 --> 00:02:02,000
Please forgive me, Emma.

29
00:02:03,300 --> 00:02:07,500
Danilo, what happened
to Emma isn't your fault.

30
00:02:10,367 --> 00:02:11,433
No.

31
00:02:11,567 --> 00:02:16,067
- I can't leave Emma alone here.
- No, Danilo! Danilo!

32
00:02:16,233 --> 00:02:18,600
I know it's not easy.

33
00:02:18,733 --> 00:02:20,900
I know it hurts.

34
00:02:21,033 --> 00:02:25,567
But we need to think about
what's best for Emma.

35
00:02:25,700 --> 00:02:27,167
And also for Mookie.

36
00:02:28,933 --> 00:02:30,800
Don't worry.

37
00:02:30,933 --> 00:02:33,900
I'll make sure that she'll
be taken good care of here.

38
00:02:34,767 --> 00:02:39,900
But for now, we have to make
sacrifices for Emma's good.

39
00:02:44,833 --> 00:02:45,667
Danilo.

40
00:02:46,933 --> 00:02:48,600
Danilo, wait.

41
00:02:51,400 --> 00:02:52,800
Danilo!

42
00:02:54,633 --> 00:02:56,300
- Ouch!
- Ma'am, I'm sorry.

43
00:02:56,433 --> 00:02:58,600
- You're blocking the way!
- I'm sorry.

44
00:02:58,733 --> 00:03:00,100
Danilo!

45
00:03:00,233 --> 00:03:01,200
Danilo!

46
00:03:07,767 --> 00:03:09,467
Is that Ma'am Olive?

47
00:03:12,267 --> 00:03:13,833
Did you see a dog?

48
00:03:13,967 --> 00:03:15,267
Let's look at the dog.

49
00:03:17,067 --> 00:03:18,767
Ma'am Olive?

50
00:03:18,900 --> 00:03:20,800
Did Ma'am Olive
give birth again?

51
00:03:20,967 --> 00:03:22,467
You like that?

52
00:03:22,600 --> 00:03:25,567
But that woman dresses
and carries herself differently.

53
00:03:27,333 --> 00:03:29,633
Maybe she just looks
like Ma'am Olive.

54
00:03:33,400 --> 00:03:34,800
Hi, Emma.

55
00:03:34,933 --> 00:03:38,567
I'm Andrea.
I'm your private nurse.

56
00:03:38,700 --> 00:03:42,300
Andrea, I don't know
what's happening to me.

57
00:03:42,433 --> 00:03:45,133
But I'm not insane.

58
00:03:45,267 --> 00:03:50,367
Every patient who comes here
says the same thing.

59
00:03:50,500 --> 00:03:52,000
I'm willing to get treated.

60
00:03:52,133 --> 00:03:54,200
But I don't want
to get locked up in here.

61
00:03:54,367 --> 00:03:56,000
But you need to stay here.

62
00:03:56,133 --> 00:03:57,033
You'll get better here.

63
00:03:57,167 --> 00:03:59,000
I'm begging you.

64
00:03:59,133 --> 00:04:01,900
I had not seen my daughter
for 17 years.

65
00:04:02,033 --> 00:04:03,733
We've just reunited.

66
00:04:03,867 --> 00:04:07,000
Please don't keep
me away from her.

67
00:04:07,133 --> 00:04:09,567
I'm sorry, Emma,
but you need to stay here.

68
00:04:09,700 --> 00:04:10,567
I don't want to be here.

69
00:04:10,700 --> 00:04:12,900
This place will drive me
crazy even more.

70
00:04:13,033 --> 00:04:15,467
Bring me back to my husband,

71
00:05:01,433 --> 00:05:03,700
This isn't enough
for the kindness

72
00:05:03,833 --> 00:05:05,167
your sister had shown me.

73
00:05:16,567 --> 00:05:21,267
Ma'am, you came
to the right person.

74
00:05:21,400 --> 00:05:22,467
Take a seat first.

75
00:05:23,733 --> 00:05:27,000
- Jade?
- I know. I know, Andrea.

76
00:05:27,133 --> 00:05:29,833
Astrid told me everything.

77
00:05:29,967 --> 00:05:33,900
I heard you embezzled
money from Artemis Pharmacy.

78
00:05:34,067 --> 00:05:37,867
And yet, my sister
Olive forgave you.

79
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:42,167
You would probably be in jail
now if it weren't for her.

80
00:05:42,300 --> 00:05:44,933
Ma'am, everyone here doesn't
know anything about that.

81
00:05:45,067 --> 00:05:46,633
Someone might hear you.

82
00:05:46,767 --> 00:05:49,233
Don't worry, Andrea.

83
00:05:49,367 --> 00:05:53,633
Your secret is safe with me.

84
00:05:53,767 --> 00:05:57,200
That's if you'll cooperate.

85
00:05:57,333 --> 00:05:58,800
Which I know you will.

86
00:05:58,933 --> 00:06:00,967
That's why I brought Emma here.

87
00:06:02,567 --> 00:06:04,133
Yes, Ma'am.

88
00:06:04,267 --> 00:06:06,400
You can count on me.

89
00:06:06,533 --> 00:06:09,767
Thank you so much, Andrea.

90
00:06:09,933 --> 00:06:11,700
Get me out of here!

91
00:06:15,533 --> 00:06:17,900
That's only a down payment.

92
00:06:18,033 --> 00:06:23,267
I'll give you a bonus
if you do your job well.

93
00:06:25,567 --> 00:06:27,300
I knew it, Ma'am.

94
00:06:27,433 --> 00:06:29,833
You're as generous
as your sister.

95
00:06:29,967 --> 00:06:31,633
But wait, Ma'am.

96
00:06:31,767 --> 00:06:34,133
What do you want me to do?

97
00:06:40,033 --> 00:06:43,067
I've already mixed this
with other substances,

98
00:06:43,233 --> 00:06:45,233
so it'll have more
adverse effects.

99
00:06:46,900 --> 00:06:49,933
This place is so boring.

100
00:06:50,067 --> 00:06:54,600
I only want Emma's stay
here to be colorful.

101
00:07:32,500 --> 00:07:34,367
Dear.

102
00:07:34,500 --> 00:07:36,600
Why are you just staring there?
Why haven't you eaten yet?

103
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:41,167
Well, Dad...

104
00:07:41,300 --> 00:07:43,533
I'm just thinking about Mom.

105
00:07:45,900 --> 00:07:49,800
I wonder if what she's eating
there is also delicious.

106
00:07:49,967 --> 00:07:52,500
Don't worry, dear.
She'll do fine.

107
00:07:54,867 --> 00:07:57,433
I'm just thinking...

108
00:07:57,567 --> 00:07:59,200
did we do the right thing

109
00:07:59,333 --> 00:08:02,933
in putting Mom
in a psychiatric clinic?

110
00:08:03,067 --> 00:08:07,933
I wasn't able to go
out for 17 years.

111
00:08:08,067 --> 00:08:11,533
I felt I was in prison.

112
00:08:11,667 --> 00:08:14,833
I don't want Mom to
feel the same thing.

113
00:08:22,267 --> 00:08:23,333
Come here, dear.

114
00:08:24,700 --> 00:08:26,033
Look at me.

115
00:08:31,567 --> 00:08:34,400
Dear, I know
it's also not easy for you

116
00:08:34,533 --> 00:08:39,433
to be separated from your mom.

117
00:08:39,567 --> 00:08:42,567
But that's for your mom's good.

118
00:08:42,700 --> 00:08:45,967
And also for your good,
for our good.

119
00:08:50,967 --> 00:08:53,800
I just miss Mom.

120
00:08:57,933 --> 00:08:58,933
Me, too, dear.

121
00:09:00,633 --> 00:09:04,300
I miss your mother, too.

122
00:09:04,433 --> 00:09:08,967
Those few months
she has to stay there

123
00:09:09,100 --> 00:09:13,367
feel like forever for us.

124
00:09:14,600 --> 00:09:20,800
Let's just hope your mom won't
stay long in that place.

125
00:09:20,933 --> 00:09:23,833
And she'll be with us
again soon.

126
00:09:25,833 --> 00:09:27,233
Don't worry.

127
00:09:31,500 --> 00:09:34,567
Come on. Let's eat.

128
00:09:36,233 --> 00:09:38,467
<i>You can increase the dosage
the medications</i>

129
00:09:38,600 --> 00:09:40,400
<i> for better efficacy.</i>

130
00:09:40,533 --> 00:09:43,567
<i> Make it Emma's daily vitamins.</i>

131
00:09:52,867 --> 00:09:55,300
It's time for your meds.

132
00:09:56,500 --> 00:09:57,967
I saw you and Jade.

133
00:09:58,100 --> 00:10:00,167
You're in cahoots!

134
00:10:00,300 --> 00:10:01,600
You'll do something to me.

135
00:10:01,767 --> 00:10:03,433
You're planning
something against me.

136
00:10:05,200 --> 00:10:06,500
You're just being paranoid.

137
00:10:07,167 --> 00:10:08,567
Ma'am Jade wants
to take care of you.

138
00:10:08,700 --> 00:10:10,033
Liar!

139
00:10:10,733 --> 00:10:14,133
You want to drive me crazy
so I won't see my family!

140
00:10:14,267 --> 00:10:15,900
She's blaming me
for Olive's death.

141
00:10:16,033 --> 00:10:18,433
It wasn't my fault!
Let go of me!

142
00:10:19,633 --> 00:10:20,467
Stop!

143
00:10:21,533 --> 00:10:23,400
- Don't!
- Your mind just made that up.

144
00:10:23,533 --> 00:10:24,633
So you need medicine!

145
00:10:44,300 --> 00:10:47,133
Stop. I don't want it anymore.

146
00:10:49,933 --> 00:10:52,600
<i> Make her completely crazy!</i>

147
00:10:52,733 --> 00:10:54,167
They are demons. Kill them!

148
00:10:54,300 --> 00:10:59,500
They will kill you.
They are evil!

149
00:10:59,633 --> 00:11:00,533
I don't want to be here.

150
00:11:00,667 --> 00:11:02,233
This place will drive
me crazy even more!

151
00:11:02,367 --> 00:11:06,100
Bring me back to my husband.

152
00:11:06,233 --> 00:11:08,633
<i> They will kill you!</i>

153
00:11:08,800 --> 00:11:10,500
<i>- Kill them!
- They will kill you!</i>

154
00:11:10,633 --> 00:11:13,000
<i>- They are evil people.
- They'll kill you.</i>

155
00:11:13,133 --> 00:11:16,533
<i>- Don't let them kill you.
- They are demons. Kill them!</i>

156
00:11:16,667 --> 00:11:19,200
<i>They are evil people.
They'll kill you.</i>

157
00:11:19,333 --> 00:11:21,167
<i> They are demons. Kill them!</i>

158
00:11:28,233 --> 00:11:30,933
Don't you see? She's Olive!

159
00:11:31,067 --> 00:11:36,867
Ligaya enjoyed Cebu so much.

160
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:38,933
She became hypertensive
after eating a lot!

161
00:11:39,067 --> 00:11:41,800
We rushed her to the hospital.

162
00:11:41,967 --> 00:11:44,500
The doctor didn't allow her
to travel.

163
00:11:44,633 --> 00:11:45,800
She's already doing okay.

164
00:11:46,700 --> 00:11:49,800
But is what I heard true?

165
00:11:50,600 --> 00:11:52,567
Emma's in a mental clinic?

166
00:11:55,200 --> 00:11:57,100
Yes, but...

167
00:11:57,233 --> 00:11:58,900
don't worry.

168
00:11:59,033 --> 00:12:01,900
The doctors are taking
good care of her.

169
00:12:02,033 --> 00:12:06,100
I'll tell Mom about it.

170
00:12:06,233 --> 00:12:08,700
I'm sorry about what happened
to Aunt Emma, Mooks,

171
00:12:08,833 --> 00:12:09,800
Uncle Danilo,

172
00:12:11,133 --> 00:12:12,700
Poor Emma.

173
00:12:12,833 --> 00:12:17,733
Emma has gone insane
after going through a lot.

174
00:12:21,867 --> 00:12:23,967
Maybe it's better

175
00:12:24,100 --> 00:12:27,100
if we keep Emma's condition
from Mom for now.

176
00:12:28,133 --> 00:12:30,367
Her hypertension
might get worse.

177
00:12:31,133 --> 00:12:33,200
Yeah.

178
00:12:33,333 --> 00:12:34,767
By the way,

179
00:12:34,900 --> 00:12:39,567
I also brought yours and Emma's
stuff left at home.

180
00:12:41,600 --> 00:12:44,867
I'm sure Mom
will be glad to see this.

181
00:12:45,833 --> 00:12:48,400
Dad, can we visit Mom?

182
00:12:49,367 --> 00:12:54,600
When I was lonely
in Mommy Olive's house,

183
00:12:54,733 --> 00:12:57,667
Mom would always
go to my room.

184
00:12:57,800 --> 00:13:02,133
And she would often read
this storybook to me.

185
00:13:03,067 --> 00:13:05,100
And I'd feel happy after that.

186
00:13:06,500 --> 00:13:08,867
I also want
to make her happy now.

187
00:13:11,100 --> 00:13:13,867
- Do you want to see it? Look.
- Oh, yeah.

188
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:16,633
This story is beautiful.
Promise.

189
00:13:16,767 --> 00:13:20,100
- There.
- Once upon a time...

190
00:13:20,233 --> 00:13:24,267
That's Mommy Lily and Rosie.

191
00:13:30,333 --> 00:13:31,667
Hey.

192
00:13:31,800 --> 00:13:33,800
You must behave.

193
00:13:33,933 --> 00:13:36,533
Don't try anything.
Your family's here.

194
00:13:36,667 --> 00:13:38,533
They're planning
something evil against me.

195
00:13:38,667 --> 00:13:45,200
Don't let them get near me.

196
00:13:45,333 --> 00:13:47,167
They're planning something
bad against me.

197
00:13:49,667 --> 00:13:50,900
They'll kill me.

198
00:13:52,233 --> 00:13:53,500
They'll kill me.

199
00:13:58,867 --> 00:13:59,800
They'll kill me.

200
00:14:05,300 --> 00:14:07,933
I wonder how Mom's doing.

201
00:14:08,067 --> 00:14:09,767
I hope she's doing okay.

202
00:14:09,900 --> 00:14:13,133
I'm sure Aunt Emma
misses you, too.

203
00:14:13,267 --> 00:14:16,800
I really hope she'll be happy
when she sees this storybook.

204
00:14:21,800 --> 00:14:23,867
- Emma? Emma!
- Mom!

205
00:14:25,733 --> 00:14:26,833
Mom, how are you?

206
00:14:26,967 --> 00:14:28,733
Are you doing okay here?

207
00:14:34,667 --> 00:14:38,133
You're planning something
bad against me.

208
00:14:38,267 --> 00:14:39,900
No, Mom.

209
00:14:40,033 --> 00:14:41,433
Look, Mom.

210
00:14:41,567 --> 00:14:42,833
I brought this storybook.

211
00:14:42,967 --> 00:14:45,433
Do you remember this?

212
00:14:45,567 --> 00:14:47,533
Look, Mom.

213
00:14:47,667 --> 00:14:49,600
Lily and Rosie.

214
00:14:49,733 --> 00:14:51,800
Do you remember Mommy Lily?

215
00:14:51,933 --> 00:14:54,267
Mommy Lily looked for Rosie.

216
00:14:54,400 --> 00:14:57,667
Then, Rosie's fear disappeared.

217
00:14:59,267 --> 00:15:04,633
So, Mom, no matter how
scared you are,

218
00:15:04,800 --> 00:15:09,033
I hope it disappears now
that I'm here.

219
00:15:09,167 --> 00:15:10,133
We're here.

220
00:15:12,433 --> 00:15:14,133
- Emma!
- Wait!

221
00:15:14,267 --> 00:15:15,767
- Mookie!
- You're a monster!

222
00:15:15,900 --> 00:15:17,933
- I'll kill you!
- Emma!

223
00:15:22,900 --> 00:15:23,667
Emma!

224
00:15:23,800 --> 00:15:25,767
- You'll kill me!
- No, Emma.

225
00:15:25,900 --> 00:15:26,867
You'll kill me!

226
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:28,400
Hold on.

227
00:15:28,533 --> 00:15:30,833
- Mookie, please!
- Mookie!

228
00:15:30,967 --> 00:15:34,267
- Emma, let go of her!
- Let go of me! Demon!

229
00:15:34,400 --> 00:15:36,100
You are demons!

230
00:15:36,267 --> 00:15:37,200
- Emma, wait!
- Demons!

231
00:15:37,333 --> 00:15:39,033
You're going to kill me!
You're going to kill me!

232
00:15:39,167 --> 00:15:40,033
- Demons!
- We won't kill you!

233
00:15:40,167 --> 00:15:41,900
You'll kill me!

234
00:15:42,033 --> 00:15:43,100
I'll kill you!

235
00:15:43,233 --> 00:15:44,300
I'll kill you!

236
00:15:44,433 --> 00:15:47,133
Demon!

237
00:15:47,267 --> 00:15:48,533
Demons!

238
00:15:48,667 --> 00:15:52,767
I'll kill you all!

239
00:15:52,900 --> 00:15:54,067
- Emma.
- I'll kill you all!

240
00:15:54,200 --> 00:15:59,667
I'll kill you all!

241
00:16:02,633 --> 00:16:04,633
Mookie, dear.

242
00:16:04,767 --> 00:16:05,900
Are you okay?

243
00:16:09,167 --> 00:16:10,300
Mookie.

244
00:16:23,400 --> 00:16:24,733
Mookie, are you okay?

245
00:16:25,533 --> 00:16:26,933
That was unbelievable!

246
00:16:27,733 --> 00:16:31,467
Let go of me!

247
00:16:31,600 --> 00:16:38,133
They're going to kill me!

248
00:16:38,267 --> 00:16:39,300
Go on!

249
00:16:39,433 --> 00:16:41,533
Put her inside! Hurry!

250
00:16:42,967 --> 00:16:44,100
Put her inside!

251
00:16:46,233 --> 00:16:47,800
Put her inside!

252
00:16:53,233 --> 00:16:55,400
<i>I used to be
Ma'am Olive's caretaker</i>

253
00:16:55,533 --> 00:16:57,300
in her house in Manila.

254
00:16:57,433 --> 00:17:00,600
Ma'am Olive had become
more irritable at that time,

255
00:17:00,733 --> 00:17:03,200
especially when
her child died.

256
00:17:03,333 --> 00:17:05,767
Olive lost a child?

257
00:17:05,900 --> 00:17:07,233
That's Emma!

258
00:17:18,467 --> 00:17:19,433
Hello?

259
00:17:28,567 --> 00:17:31,167
No!

260
00:17:39,800 --> 00:17:41,667
Darn you!

261
00:17:41,800 --> 00:17:43,967
You almost killed me!

262
00:17:44,100 --> 00:17:48,067
And because of what you did,
go and rot here for days!

263
00:17:48,200 --> 00:17:49,300
I don't want to be here.

264
00:17:49,467 --> 00:17:51,900
They will kill me.
There's a demon here!

265
00:17:52,033 --> 00:17:53,300
Then good.

266
00:17:53,433 --> 00:17:55,867
So that we'll be in peace!

267
00:17:56,000 --> 00:17:58,867
I don't want to be here!
Get me out of here!

268
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:02,300
Do you think you still
have a family

269
00:18:02,433 --> 00:18:04,700
after what you did to them?

270
00:18:04,833 --> 00:18:07,333
You'll rot in here!

271
00:18:07,467 --> 00:18:10,367
You'll die!

272
00:18:10,500 --> 00:18:14,233
I don't want to be here!
I don't want to!

273
00:18:14,367 --> 00:18:17,167
They'll kill me here.

274
00:18:17,300 --> 00:18:21,933
Where are you going?
Let me go with you!

275
00:18:22,100 --> 00:18:26,333
Let me go with you!

276
00:18:26,467 --> 00:18:29,267
Don't leave me here!
They'll kill me!

277
00:18:31,933 --> 00:18:33,633
They'll kill me!

278
00:18:40,633 --> 00:18:44,367
Get me out of here! They'll kill
me here! Let me out!

279
00:18:47,733 --> 00:18:49,000
You know what...

280
00:18:50,600 --> 00:18:53,367
I used to feel safe
whenever I was with Mommy Emma.

281
00:18:55,267 --> 00:18:56,233
But now...

282
00:18:57,467 --> 00:18:59,333
she's also scary.

283
00:19:00,233 --> 00:19:02,167
She's like Mommy Olive.

284
00:19:05,300 --> 00:19:08,000
I also can't believe it.

285
00:19:08,133 --> 00:19:11,833
The nurses said that Emma
was doing okay already.

286
00:19:11,967 --> 00:19:13,767
She has improved a lot.

287
00:19:13,900 --> 00:19:16,433
I don't know
why she became like that.

288
00:19:18,033 --> 00:19:24,900
So, does it mean Mom hates
us, that's why she did that?

289
00:19:28,100 --> 00:19:29,833
Maybe.

290
00:19:29,967 --> 00:19:33,300
Maybe Emma's really upset

291
00:19:33,433 --> 00:19:36,767
that we confined her
to a psychiatric clinic.

292
00:19:36,900 --> 00:19:40,767
It's probably better if you
don't go to Emma for now.

293
00:19:40,900 --> 00:19:43,400
It's also for Mookie's safety.

294
00:19:43,533 --> 00:19:46,933
Your Aunt Jade is right, Mookie.

295
00:19:47,067 --> 00:19:51,333
You might end up reliving your
trauma when you see Emma again.

296
00:19:52,800 --> 00:19:56,300
Baby girl, maybe
you should rest for now.

297
00:19:56,433 --> 00:19:58,700
Are you feeling better?

298
00:19:58,833 --> 00:20:01,700
- A little bit.
- That's good.

299
00:20:01,867 --> 00:20:03,033
Bring her to her room.

300
00:20:03,167 --> 00:20:05,533
- Let's go, dear.
- Get some rest.

301
00:20:29,500 --> 00:20:31,033
Who are you?

302
00:20:31,167 --> 00:20:34,733
- Why do you keep on calling...
- How are you, Jade Caparas.

303
00:20:34,900 --> 00:20:36,933
I've finally found you.

304
00:20:37,067 --> 00:20:38,833
I don't know you.

305
00:20:38,967 --> 00:20:40,633
Stop calling me.

306
00:21:02,100 --> 00:21:02,867
Danilo.

307
00:21:04,100 --> 00:21:05,100
- Jade.
- It's late.

308
00:21:05,233 --> 00:21:06,367
Why are you still here?

309
00:21:07,667 --> 00:21:09,000
Why aren't you
getting some rest?

310
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:11,867
Look. You're so sweaty.

311
00:21:12,733 --> 00:21:13,300
No.

312
00:21:13,767 --> 00:21:15,067
I'm just looking
for a distraction because...

313
00:21:19,100 --> 00:21:20,500
I want to forget about Emma.

314
00:21:23,333 --> 00:21:25,500
I feel bad for my daughter.

315
00:21:26,467 --> 00:21:28,333
She badly wanted
to see her mother.

316
00:21:29,267 --> 00:21:30,567
And that's what happened.

317
00:21:33,133 --> 00:21:34,967
You know, Danilo...

318
00:21:36,333 --> 00:21:40,667
maybe we should leave Emma be in
the psychiatric clinic for now.

319
00:21:42,300 --> 00:21:47,167
But you have to take
care of yourself, Danilo.

320
00:21:48,300 --> 00:21:50,033
Don't tire yourself
out too much.

321
00:21:51,833 --> 00:21:53,800
You might end up
getting sick, too.

322
00:21:54,700 --> 00:21:57,267
Don't forget
that Mookie needs you.

323
00:21:58,333 --> 00:21:59,167
And...

324
00:22:00,200 --> 00:22:03,367
I'm here to help both of you.

325
00:22:05,300 --> 00:22:06,633
That's the case.

326
00:22:06,767 --> 00:22:08,367
I feel shy...

327
00:22:09,333 --> 00:22:11,233
because you've done
more than enough.

328
00:22:11,367 --> 00:22:13,533
You're spending
all your time on us.

329
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:20,700
Maybe others deserve your care
and attention more than we do.

330
00:22:22,033 --> 00:22:27,267
Do you mean a boyfriend?

331
00:22:28,033 --> 00:22:30,133
Well...

332
00:22:30,267 --> 00:22:31,800
I'm not going to deny.

333
00:22:32,600 --> 00:22:35,167
Some have feelings for me.

334
00:22:35,300 --> 00:22:37,700
Some are courting me.

335
00:22:37,833 --> 00:22:44,500
But the thing is,
I don't like any of them.

336
00:22:49,767 --> 00:22:51,133
Sometimes,

337
00:22:53,867 --> 00:22:57,100
the ones you like

338
00:22:57,233 --> 00:23:01,000
are the ones
that aren't meant for you.

339
00:23:01,133 --> 00:23:02,100
Because...

340
00:23:05,000 --> 00:23:07,167
someone else
already owns them.

341
00:23:24,933 --> 00:23:26,000
How are you?

342
00:23:27,367 --> 00:23:29,033
How dare you touch me?

343
00:23:29,500 --> 00:23:30,967
Who are you? I don't know you!

344
00:23:31,100 --> 00:23:33,767
You disappeared
after you drained me of money!

345
00:23:33,900 --> 00:23:36,200
You weren't answering my calls.

346
00:23:36,333 --> 00:23:39,467
So, you're that person
who keeps calling me.

347
00:23:39,600 --> 00:23:41,433
Are you sure it was Emma?

348
00:23:41,567 --> 00:23:43,767
I clearly remember Emma's face.

349
00:23:43,900 --> 00:23:45,000
She's so pitiful.

350
00:23:45,133 --> 00:23:47,400
I think she's not
getting better.

351
00:23:47,533 --> 00:23:49,133
She's even getting worse.

352
00:23:50,767 --> 00:23:51,967
Emma escaped?

353
00:23:52,100 --> 00:23:54,100
Danilo will definitely
look for Emma

354
00:23:54,233 --> 00:23:56,300
when he finds out
his wife is missing!

355
00:23:57,833 --> 00:23:58,667
Help me.

356
00:23:58,800 --> 00:23:59,833
Help me.

357
00:23:59,967 --> 00:24:00,900
Is that you, Emma?

358
00:24:01,033 --> 00:24:02,033
They'll kill me!

359
00:24:02,167 --> 00:24:05,033
Help me! I'm scared!
